list.item:
V. The necessity of subjection;
Wherefore ye must needs be subject.
And

VI. The nature of that necessity;
it is not of prudence, but of
Conscience.

div.p:
Secondly, Those which refer to matters Civil, are reducible to such as these;
I. Harsh Administration.
II. Pretences of Competition of Power; and the like.

A miserable hope, if this be all; 
for Thon shalt be brought to Iudgment:
That's the second Proposition.

list.item:
I. Israels requital towards God;
implyed in the expostulation;
Do ye thus requite?
